          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-1" n="1">Tom for a Goose You keep but base Quills</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-2" n="2">They're fit for nothing else but Pasquills</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-3" n="3">I've often heard it from the Wise,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-4" n="4">That Inflamations in the Eyes</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-5" n="5">Will quickly fall upon the Tongue</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-6" n="6">And thence as fam'd John Bunyan sung,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-7" n="7">From out the Pen will presently</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-8" n="8">On Paper dribble daintily.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-9" n="9">Suppose I call'd You goose, it is hard</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-10" n="10">One Word shou'd stick thus in Y<hi rend="superscript">rÌ£</hi> Gizard</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-11" n="11">You're My Goose and no other man's</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-12" n="12">And You know all my Geese are Swans:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-13" n="13">Only One scurvy thing I find</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-14" n="14">Swans sing when dying, Geese when Blind.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-15" n="15">But now I smoak where lies the slander</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-16" n="16">I call'd You Goose instead of Gander;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-17" n="17">For that Dear Tom, ne're fret and Vex</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-18" n="18">I'm sure You cackle like the sex.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-19" n="19">I know the Gander allways goes</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-20" n="20">With a Quill stuck across his Nose;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-21" n="21">So Your Eternal Pen is still,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-22" n="22">Or in Your Claw, or in Your Bill.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-23" n="23">But whither You can Tread or Hatch</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-24" n="24">I've something else to do than Watch.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-25" n="25">As for You're writing I am Dead</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-26" n="26">I leave it for the second head.</l>
            <l rend="indent(3)" xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-27" n="27">||Dean'ry house</l>
            <l rend="indent(4)" xml:id="swift-982-CWJS-line-28" n="28">|||Oct<hi rend="superscript">br</hi>: 27<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>: 1718.</l>
